# reality.word — what a reality IS: all its branches, the durable whole.
# Axiom: it bottoms out in the host (seed/realityIdentity.js — the realityId is I_AM's key id;
# seed/past/fact/chainRoots.js — the realityRoot, a hash over the branch roots). Descends from
# word.word, base.word, chain.word, branch.word; every word in it is grounded (reality, branch,
# fact, chain, hash, main). The realityId and the signing of its seal wait for `name`, above this.

A reality is all of its branches.
Every fact is in it, on some chain, on some branch.
A reality has a hash over its branches. The seal binds the whole, and no other reality makes it.
A reality lasts. Its facts do not pass, and a branch diverges within it, never beyond it.
The main is the first branch of a reality. Every other branch forks from one already in it.
